I have such a positive review of one of your employees whom I felt in my opinion is one of the most wonderful and delightful person whom I have ever met. My child turned 12 on February 25, 2021 and to celebrate we came down to water tower place hoping to grab a bite to eat. However we were extremely disappointed when we realized that the great atmosphere and variety of restaurants on the mezzanine level were all gone ! We were shocked to say the least and saddened. So on our way out of the water towel we noticed that wow Bao was open and my child wanted to try some of the food from there. Upon stopping their we met a young lady by the name of Kayla she was very empathetic to our disappointment and also when she found out that it was my child’s birthday she wished her a very happy birthday and made her feel special on her very special day! Kayla had a wonderful positive disposition , she was warm and welcoming and the fact that she took the time to serve us made us feel better , and it really made our day. They say first impressions are lasting impression and I must say this is very true! The impression she made on my family will last a lifetime and I am grateful and thankful that Wow Bao hired her because she brings a positive overall feeling to this restaurant and it’s great tasting food and warm-welcoming employees! Thanks Kayla and thank you Wow Bao!!

The cashier was super helpful, and I ordered a teriyaki chicken bao, BBQ pork bao, and chicken dumplings (which came with a soy dipping sauce). All were flavorful and moist, similar to what you'd get in most good Asian restaurants. It made for a small but filling dinner. I would totally go back to try other flavors.

It is not by choice that I find myself in Chicago in February. But since I am here, what better way to dive in than hit up Wow Bao?! Ordered their combo 2 buns and broth. Loved their bbq pork bun but not so much the kung pao bun. Not a fan of peanuts in buns. Otherwise, it was great. Hot broth in a coffee cup and a warm steamed bun in the freezing Chicago winter, suddenly the cold weather isn't so cold anymore.
Very nice service.  A bowl and a bao makes a very filling lunch. Spice kung pao chicken was at the top of my personal heat range, but still good.

I love this place. I used to come all the time and try the different Baos. My favorite is definitely the chicken curry, and the limited edition dessert ones like apple pie and pumpkin. Very quick service and the line moves fast. Also order on their touchscreen displays to skip the wait.

Two things you must have at least once here, the teriyaki bao, and the chocolate one. It's such a simple concept, but these can easily become addictive, especially since they come in such a compact form. This is one of the most convenient locations too, because it's right by the front entrance so you can quickly get in and out without dealing with tons of tourists.
Pork wow bao, and chiken is the best!!

Great place to grab a quick snack after shopping.  It's good stuff, but I'm a big guy and for me to get filled up I need more than half a dozen. My favorites are the beef, pork, and chicken kungpao, in that order. I haven't tried their rice bowls, but for something like that I'd rather eat at Panda Express.

I love me some hot Asian buns! Can not get enough of them at times. Some of my favorites there include the BBQ Pork Bun, Spicy Kung Pao Chicken Bun & the Pot Stickers. They also have cool seasonal dessert buns! Nothing better than SWEET ASIAN BUNS!! One of my favorites is the Pumpkin Bun.

This is one of their most fun locations, because I always get to come in and see the staff having a great time, and the effect rubs off on you and puts you in a good mood. Located at the entrance of The Water Tower Mall, it's a very convenient location and great customer service and the fantastic food selection that we all know and love.
It's quick and super tasty.  Become a member of Lettuce Entertain you for great savings.
Love this place for baos. They are so fluffy and soft, yum. My favorites are the edamame and BBQ. Thei salad is great too.

I have only had the thai herb broth, but it is addictive!  I have food allergies, so I called ahead and asked what I could eat.  They were very helpful finding something safe for me.   When I was there to order, I asked again just because I have had accidents in the past.  They were very pleasant and accommodating. The soup itself was AWESOME!  It tasted like lemon grass and ginger heaven.  It's a very quick meal and the service was great.  I will be going back.:)

Great place to grab a quick snack, my favorite is the thai curry chicken. They also have bowls using the meat filling for the baos and I like that they have the option to use cabbage instead of rice for the bowl.

Wow! The baos here taste really good, which is surprising because it's not easy to make traditional chinese steamed buns well. Chinatown has some, of course, but to find them in the city, right at Water Tower place, is a pleasant surprise.  I personally love all their baos with meat in them. Eat them while it's piping hot to really enjoy the tenderness of the bun, coupled with the steaming hot meat inside. It makes for a great snack to energize you before hitting the shops. On a cold winter's day, this is the perfect warm-me-up food.

LOVE wow bao!  This is a frquent stop for me.  This location is in the lobby of the watertower place and very easy to get to on a crowded michigan avenue.  What's even better is they have kiosks you can order from (if you're paying my credit card), and you can avoid the line.  You'll be in and out in a few minutes, with a meal you can eat as you walk!  perfect!

This Wow Bao location is my favorite, simply because they have the best froyo. Its subtly tart and not too creamy- just the way I like it. Also, like all other Wow Bao, this one also have the self-served kiosks as well as full-serve. It can get crowded, due to it's prime location in the lobby of the water tower place, but you always get speedy service, and you can most-likely find a spot to eat one floor above. Also, the food is delicious (Try the dessert bao!), and if you check-in on social media, you'll get some sort of discount. And if you pay attention on Wednesdays, they post a secret word on facebook which will grant you free baos!

Delicious, doughy little boas are exactly what you get from Wow Boa. Located in the mall foyer, this is a popular lunch spot and an good option if you're on the move and need something you can eat in your hands.  If you're on FourSquare, these guys rock with a buy one, get one free perk. Two tasty boas for $1.87 - awesome.  The desert boas are too sweet for me but the Mongolian Beef and the Green Thai Curry normally hit the spot.

Wow Bao recently catered an event for me and I really enjoyed working with their catering team. They were very helpful and quick to respond to questions. Overall I think the food is convenient and tasty. The offer side options like a noodle salad and potstickers but I would stick with the baos which are very filling and flavorful. My favorite bao is the BBQ beef but I also like the grilled veggie one.

What a taste! The bao is good, I had one chocolate and one spicy kung pao chicken, they're tasty, but none can beat up my joy the moment I sip the herb broth. Man, that was a few minutes of deliciousness !!
I discovered Wow Bao during my visit in Chicago and kept going back for more. Loved the spicy baos!

I like wowbao. Its something i had not tried till this year.  I always thought the bao's seemed little and maybe pricey until i visited. Now i realize that they are an excellent deal.  That little bao really fills you up.  The teriyaki chicken is my favorite.  This location was average amongst the various chicago locations,  the service is average, but the baos or the best part
I love the coconut, edamame and chocolate baos!   The kiosks are super easy to use.
Every time i come to Chicago i stop here for a bbq bun. Awesome snack! Why don't you open in Minnesota?!!
This is a stable for me everytime I visit Water Tower.  It's simple and delicious food that is perfect to grab and go while you shop!  The bowls and the Boa's are yummy--kung pao is my favorite.
Sometimes their service is a little poor and disorganized but I'm always satisfied with their Baos. Very delicious
